I made this for my in- laws on Christmas day and everyone LOVED it. First of all, it is VERY easy to make. I sliced the bread and whipped up the egg mixture before I went out for Christmas Eve dinner. When I got home, I assembled put the bread in the egg mixture and soaked it overnight. I baked it in the oven as directed and it came out PERFECT! It had a little kick from the egg nog, and was moist and fluffy on the inside and toasted perfectly on the outside. The compote is the ideal complement to the dish. The cranberries cut the sweetness from the apple and sugar. I think the secret is to use a thick, dense bread. That way the french toast will not be soggy. I bought a country white loaf and sliced it myself. I can see how a thin bread might be mushy. I am trying it with challah for New Year's Day brunch because I have egg nog and compote left over.

