Rating: 3
I made this recipe on Christmas morning - it was the perfect wintry mix of delicious and nostalgic flavors. I liked being able to make it the night before so the time spent cooking in the morning was minimal. All I had to do was pop it in the oven and reheat the compote. This way, it took less time than even "plain old" french toast would have taken to prepare in the morning and was so much more impressive. I did find the compote took much longer to cook than the recipe stated. Perhaps I cut the fruit too large. It was wonderful, though, and kept getting better with each reheating. There was enough left over to serve as a side dish with a future dinner and as a topping for another dessert! I was afraid that soaking the bread in the eggnog mixture overnight would make it too soggy in the middle, but the baking (rather than grilling) took care of that. I would make this again any time I can find eggnog in the store!

